sp.p:
[Drawing herself up.]Of course it is, child;  
Who else should it be! [Aside.] I knew 
I should make them open their eyes.

An idle tale ; a senseless fable told by croning gossips ; 
A treasure often sought, but never found ; and some do say 'tis
death to seek it.

div.stage:
[All unmask ; Rodolphe in doing so, throws off his domino; 
draws his sword, and places himself before Amina.
Chord.]

sp.p:
Certainly ; of course, just which ever you please, my 
dear, wine butt or beer barrel, its all the same to me ; 
you know you will cackle.
